@startuml 12B-state-analysis-job
' CVerify — analysis_jobs.Status lifecycle (repository analysis)
' Verified against:
'   Modules/SourceCode/Entities/AnalysisJob.cs:28              (Status = "Queued", no enum, MaxLength 50)
'   Modules/SourceCode/Services/RepositoryAnalysisService.cs
'       :120,:169   new AnalysisJob { Status = "Queued", CurrentStep = "Queued" }
'       :92-106,:336,:2251  activeStates membership tests
'       :342        CancelAnalysisAsync -> job.Status = "Cancelled"
'       :389,:524,:673,:912  cooperative cancellation checks (`if (job.Status == "Cancelled")`)
'       :534        job.Status = "RunningAgents"
'       :724,:981   job.Status = "Failed"
'       :917        job.Status = "Completed"
'       :945        freshJob.Status = "TimedOut"
'       :1017,:304  terminalStates = { Completed, Failed, Cancelled, TimedOut }
'       :1102       RetryTaskAsync -> job.Status = "Queued"
'       :1521-1560  UpdateJobStateAsync(job, status, ...)  <-- see discrepancy note
'   Modules/SourceCode/BackgroundWorkers/AnalysisQueueRecoverySweeper.cs:39,:51,:75,:90-101
'   Modules/SourceCode/Controllers/RepositoryAnalysisController.cs:51,:76,:304
'   docs/architecture/reverse-engineered/GROUND-TRUTH.md  §5.4 (in-process non-durable queues)

title analysis_jobs.Status — repository AnalysisJob lifecycle (plain string column, no enum)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor<<terminal>> #FFECEC
  BackgroundColor<<unreachable>> #F2F2F2
}

[*] --> Queued : RepositoryAnalysisService\n(job created, enqueued on IRepositoryAnalysisQueue)

state Queued
state RunningAgents
state Completed <<terminal>>
state Failed <<terminal>>
state Cancelled <<terminal>>
state TimedOut <<terminal>>

state "Intermediate step states" as INTERMEDIATE #F2F2F2 {
  state Preparing <<unreachable>>
  state CloningRepository <<unreachable>>
  state DetectingTechnologyStack <<unreachable>>
  state SamplingCode <<unreachable>>
  state AggregatingResults <<unreachable>>
  state SavingReport <<unreachable>>
}

Queued --> RunningAgents : ProcessJobAsync dispatches tasks\n(RepositoryAnalysisService.cs:534)
Queued --> INTERMEDIATE : UpdateJobStateAsync(job, "Preparing" | …)
INTERMEDIATE --> RunningAgents
INTERMEDIATE --> Failed
RunningAgents --> Completed : all tasks finished (:917)
RunningAgents --> Failed : task/aggregation error (:724, :981)
RunningAgents --> TimedOut : job watchdog exceeded (:945)\nrepo.LatestAnalysisStatus = "TimedOut"
Queued --> Cancelled : CancelAnalysisAsync (:342)\nonly while Status is in activeStates
RunningAgents --> Cancelled : CancelAnalysisAsync (:342)

Failed --> Queued : RetryTaskAsync (:1102)\nresets task.Status = "Queued" (:1048)\nand repo.LatestAnalysisStatus = "Pending"
TimedOut --> Queued : RetryTaskAsync
Cancelled --> Queued : RetryTaskAsync

state "Recovery on restart" as REC #FFF6E6
Queued --> Failed : <b>AnalysisQueueRecoverySweeper</b>\nany activeStates job at startup ->\nStatus = "Failed",\nErrorMessage = "Job interrupted by server\nreboot or restart."
RunningAgents --> Failed : <b>AnalysisQueueRecoverySweeper</b>

Completed --> [*]
Failed --> [*]
Cancelled --> [*]
TimedOut --> [*]

note right of REC
  <b>AnalysisQueueRecoverySweeper</b> (registered hosted service)
  runs ONCE at startup, not on a timer. It sweeps every job whose
  Status is in
    { Queued, Preparing, CloningRepository, DetectingTechnologyStack,
      SamplingCode, RunningAgents, AggregatingResults, SavingReport }
  to Failed, writes an AnalysisJobEvent(Step="Failed"), and sets the
  owning repository's LatestAnalysisStatus = "Failed".
  It then sweeps orphaned repositories stuck at
  LatestAnalysisStatus = "Pending" with no active job to "Failed".
  It exists because all queues are singleton IN-PROCESS and NOT
  durable (GROUND-TRUTH §5.4).
end note

note as N_STALE #FFF0F0
  <b>Stale-comment discrepancy</b>
  AnalysisJob.cs declares only `Status = "Queued"` with MaxLength(50)
  and no value list; project documentation describes only 4 states.
  The <b>observed</b> value set across the service, controller and
  sweeper is 12:
    Queued · Preparing · CloningRepository · DetectingTechnologyStack ·
    SamplingCode · RunningAgents · AggregatingResults · SavingReport ·
    Completed · Failed · Cancelled · TimedOut
  Terminal set, asserted twice in code
  (RepositoryAnalysisService.cs:1017, RepositoryAnalysisController.cs:304):
    { Completed, Failed, Cancelled, TimedOut }.
end note

note as N_UNREACH #FFF0F0
  <b>Second discrepancy — the 6 grey states are currently unreachable.</b>
  Preparing / AggregatingResults / SavingReport are only ever passed to
  <b>UpdateJobStateAsync</b> (RepositoryAnalysisService.cs:396, :759, :820),
  and UpdateJobStateAsync (declared :1521) has <b>no call sites</b> —
  grep finds only its declaration. CloningRepository,
  DetectingTechnologyStack and SamplingCode appear ONLY inside
  `activeStates` membership arrays and are never assigned anywhere.
  The only statuses actually written to job.Status are:
  Queued, RunningAgents, Completed, Failed, Cancelled, TimedOut.
end note

note as N_PENDING
  "Pending" is NOT an analysis_jobs.Status value. It belongs to
  SourceCodeRepository.LatestAnalysisStatus, a separate column set to
  "Pending" when a job is queued (RepositoryAnalysisService.cs:129, :1113).
end note

note as N_CANCEL
  Cancellation is cooperative: the worker re-reads job.Status at
  :389, :524, :673 and :912 and aborts if it finds "Cancelled".
  UpdateJobStateAsync also re-queries the DB and throws
  OperationCanceledException if the row reads "Cancelled".
end note

@enduml
